    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Fulfill paid orders with Shopify and Notion on autopilot\n\n**Pattern:** Order Fulfillment · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nFulfill paid orders with Shopify and Notion on autopilot. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual inventory is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nOn Shopify Event → Map to Canonical Schema → Route by Event Kind → Handle 'order.paid' → Notion → Consolidate Handling → Tag Pipeline Metadata → Sort Orders Newest First → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to order fulfillment without manual effort\n- Anyone automating inventory in e-commerce\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Standardizes the process every time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Notion integration token; Shopify access token; Telegram bot token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "c5f59220-1728-8a30-f0b3-90fab5992fdb",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -290
      ],
      "id": "1320b0e8-a981-a494-58da-6274f5910a50",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your inventory process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
